[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rider critically ill after Tandragee 100 crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A rider is critically ill in hospital after crashing during a race at the Tandragee 100.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He was injured in the last lap of the Senior Support race in County Armagh on Saturday afternoon and was taken to Craigavon Area Hospital.
The remaining classes, including the Supertwin and main Superbike race were cancelled.
The Old Clare Road junction of the Markethill Road has been closed to Bellcross Road following the crash.
